The invention is best understood from the following detailed description when read in connection with the accompanying drawings. It is emphasized that, according to common practice, the various features of the drawings are not to scale. On the contrary, the dimensions of the various features are arbitrarily expanded or reduced for clarity. Included in the drawing are the following figures:


FIG. 1 is a top view illustration of an exemplary apparatus of the present invention, showing hidden internal components with dotted lines;


FIG. 2A is a side view illustration of the exemplary apparatus of FIG. 1, showing hidden internal components in dotted lines;


FIG. 2B is a cross-sectional illustration taken across line 2B--2B of FIG. 1;


FIG. 2C is a cross-sectional illustration taken across line 2C--2C of FIG. 1;


FIG. 3 is a cross-sectional illustration taken across line 3--3 of FIG. 1;


FIG. 4 is a side view schematic illustration of an exemplary batch system corporating an exemplary pass-through, wafer-processing tool of the present invention;


FIG. 5 is a top view schematic illustration of an exemplary cluster tool system incorporating two exemplary pass-through, wafer-processing tools of the present invention;


FIG. 6 is a side view schematic illustration of an exemplary linear system incorporating two, exemplary, pass-through, wafer-processing tools of the present invention;


FIG. 7 is a side view schematic illustration of an exemplary pass-through, wafer-processing tool of the present invention in which the plasma is obtained from a remote plasma source; and


FIG. 8 is a side view schematic illustration of an exemplary pass-through, wafer-processing tool of the present invention in which the plasma is generated in situ.
